========================================================================
PART B: CLUSTER ALGEBRAS AND THE FIBONACCI MUTATION
========================================================================

A CLUSTER ALGEBRA (Fomin-Zelevinsky, 2002) is generated by
CLUSTER VARIABLES that transform under MUTATIONS:

  x_k' = (x_{k-1} · x_{k+1} + 1) / x_k   (type A mutation)

For the FIBONACCI CLUSTER ALGEBRA (type A_1):
  x_{n+1} = (x_n + 1) / x_{n-1}

This generates the SEQUENCE:
  x_0, x_1, (x_1+1)/x_0, (x_1+x_0+1)/(x_0·x_1), (x_0+1)/x_1, x_0, x_1, ...

which is PERIODIC with period 5 (the PENTAGON!).

For our tournament Q_k values:
  Q_k = sin²(mπk/p) / sin²(πk/p)

Do the Q_k satisfy a MUTATION RELATION?
  Test: is Q_k' = (Q_{k-1}·Q_{k+1} + c) / Q_k for some constant c?


p=7:
  Q_{k-1}·Q_{k+1}/Q_k = ['10.5429']
