  cos(πk/p) = ['0.9907', '0.9629', '0.9172', '0.8544', '0.7757', '0.6826', '0.5767', '0.4601', '0.3349', '0.2035', '0.0682']

INSIGHT: Q_k = U_{m-1}(cos(πk/p))² where U_n is the Chebyshev 
polynomial of the second kind.

U_n(x) IS a cluster variable in the type A cluster algebra!
The Fibonacci product F_p = prod(1 + U_{m-1}(x_k)²) is an
EVALUATION of a cluster polynomial.

The CLUSTER EXCHANGE RELATION:
  U_n(x) = 2x · U_{n-1}(x) - U_{n-2}(x)

is EXACTLY the Morgan-Voyce recurrence at a specific x!
  B_m(1) = 3·B_{m-1}(1) - B_{m-2}(1)
  = U_{m-1}(3/2)... wait, let me check.

Actually: B_m(x) = U_m((2+x)/2) where U is Chebyshev-U.
So B_m(1) = U_m(3/2) and U_m(3/2) = (φ^{2(m+1)} - ψ^{2(m+1)}) / (φ²-ψ²)
which equals F_{2m+2}/√5... YES, F_{2m+1} = U_m(3/2) · √5.

This means:
  F_p = prod_{k=1}^m (1 + U_{m-1}(x_k)²)
  
  where x_k = cos(πk/p) are the Chebyshev nodes.

This is a CLUSTER INTEGRATION — evaluating a cluster polynomial
at the Chebyshev nodes and taking the product.

Verification: U_m(3/2) vs F_{2m+1}/√5:
