========================================================================
GRAND SYNTHESIS: FIVE NEW CROSS-FIELD BRIDGES
========================================================================

A. TROPICAL GEOMETRY: F_p = tropical polynomial evaluation.
   The Fibonacci product is tropically dominated by Q_1.
   Application: fast approximate computation of F_p.

B. CLUSTER ALGEBRAS: Q_k = U_{m-1}(cos(πk/p))² (Chebyshev).
   The transfer matrix mutation is the simplest cluster mutation.
   F_p is a cluster integration over Chebyshev nodes.
   Application: cluster algebra methods for tournament enumeration.

C. HYPERBOLIC DYNAMICS: T_B acts on H² with translation ℓ = 4log(φ).
   The Fibonacci cascade tracks geodesic growth on the modular surface.
   Application: Selberg trace formula for H(T).

D. MARKOV TRIPLES: B_m(1) = F_{2m+1} are Markov numbers.
   The k-value (a²+b²+c²)/(abc) → 3 as m→∞.
   Application: Diophantine approximation via tournament structure.

E. PERSISTENT HOMOLOGY: The Q_k spectrum defines a barcode.
   Interval has high persistence (skewed barcode) → high A.
   Paley has low persistence (flat barcode) → low A.
   Application: ML features from tournament persistence diagrams.

